But when I got this 2nd order home, not only were there no nuts whatsoever, there was not one cashew. When I became skeptical about my favorite, cashew chicken, I decided to change my order this time to Moo Shu  Pork, & when I went to pick up  this order, I told the owner, Lane about these latest order mistakes, expecting some restitution. His response was the worst I have ever heard from a business, quote: “it’s just cashews, there are more important things to be concerned about!” How’s that for arrogance! I have never heard that from a business when a concerned customer mentions their dissatisfaction. There was no apology, nor any offer to  make it right,  free order next time, etc. This guy & his restaurant, need to learn the basics of customer service, 101. Appalling reaction to unfulfilled order! Never again will I return, as there are plenty of Chinese cuisine restaurants in Chicago to choose from. Get a clue, Lane, you need to learn the meaning of customer service!

The egg rolls were particularly soggy and no flavor, the crab rangoon were decent but not memorable in any way, and the orange chicken was the most tasteless container of meat I've ever had in my entire life. We placed our order with more than 30 minutes before they stopped taking orders so theres really no excuse for the lack of effort and heart in this meal. $70 (after a discount) is steep for 4 people to eat Chinese and literally none of us even finished half our meal. Mon Lung is your standard, American-style takeout Chinese restaurant. It's located in a part of Chicago that doesn't really have any Chinese restaurants, so it fills a niche that way. Quality is pretty much what's expected, but the restaurant is clean and takeout is fast with food that stays piping hot. The downside was the crab rangoon which was a bit soggy and missing that crispyness we all crave. Regardless, I'll visit again when I get that craving and don't want to venture out too far, but I'd rather head down to Chinatown to get my fix.
